Module that switches off the ATI radeon card on Acer Aspire TimelineX 3820TG. Adopted from the original module for Lenovo laptops by Sylvain Joyeux.

To install:

# dkms add -m lenovo_acpi -v 0.1
# dkms build -m lenovo_acpi -v 0.1
# dkms install -m lenovo_acpi -v 0.1

Then add lenovo_acpi to /etc/modules (Debian/Ubuntu etc.) or /etc/modules.conf (Red Hat/Fedora/CentOS etc.) for auto-loading, or just run:

# modprobe lenovo_acpi
